========================================================================
                     KLARTEXT CYBERSECURITY AND DATA POLICY
========================================================================
Document ID: SEC-2026-V1
Effective Date: July 18, 2026
Classification: Internal Corporate Standard

SECTION 1: PASSWORD AND AUTHENTICATION MANAGEMENT
All employees, contractors, and third-party vendors accessing the internal 
network must utilize Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) at all times. 

Password complexity requirements are strictly enforced as follows:
1. Minimum length of 16 characters.
2. Must contain at least one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter, one 
   numerical digit, and two special characters (e.g., !, @, #, $, %).
3. Passwords must be rotated every 90 days. 
4. Re-use of any of the last 5 historical passwords is strictly prohibited.

Account Lockout Threshold:
If a user inputs an incorrect password 5 consecutive times, the account will 
be automatically locked for a duration of 30 minutes. To unlock an account 
prior to this window expiring, the employee must contact the IT Helpdesk 
directly via secure voice verification.

-------------------- PAGE BREAK / PAGE 2 --------------------

SECTION 2: DATA RETENTION, DISPOSAL, AND HARDWARE ACCUMULATION
Corporate data storage is divided into tiers based on sensitivity. 

1. Customer Personal Identifiable Information (PII): Must be encrypted 
   both at rest and in transit using AES-256 standards. PII data cannot be 
   stored on local machine drives under any circumstances.
2. Financial Records: Retained for a mandatory period of 7 years to comply 
   with regulatory tax audits, after which it must be scrubzed using certified 
   digital shredding tools.

SECTION 3: CLEAN DESK POLICY AND PHYSICAL SECURITY
Employees working within the corporate office space are required to lock 
their computer workstations (Windows Key + L or Command + Control + Q) 
any time they step away from their desks, even if only for a brief moment. 

No sensitive documents containing customer data, API access credentials, or 
source code structures may be left printed out on desks overnight. All physical 
papers must be deposited into the designated locked shredding bins located near 
the primary elevator bay.
